The fix for GHSA-8244-8vpr-vp9c / PR #28706 added `Route.continue` to keep login continuation URLs same-origin, but the current check still accepts slash-backslash URLs. A `continue` value such as `/\\evil.example/oauth-callback` passes the helper because it starts with `/` and does not start with `//`. Browser-compatible URL handling treats the backslash as a path separator for special schemes, so a `Location: /\\evil.example/oauth-callback` redirect resolves to `https://evil.example/oauth-callback`.

## Impact

An attacker can craft an Immich login URL whose continuation value bypasses the same-origin redirect check. When the authenticated-login redirect path uses the sanitized value in `redirect(307, continueUrl)`, the browser follows the response to an attacker-controlled origin. This is an incomplete fix for the public login continuation redirect class.

## Reproduction

1. Use a current main checkout at commit `e2de8c7c536cac5a673a3aa60cc998815b62d247`.
2. Observe the current helper in `web/src/lib/route.ts`:

```ts
continue: (url: string | null, fallback: string) => {
  if (!url || !url.startsWith('/') || url.startsWith('//')) {
    return fallback;
  }

  return url;
},
```

3. Decode the attacker-controlled login URL parameter:

```js
const raw = 'https://immich.local/auth/login?continue=%2F%5Cevil.example%2Foauth-callback';
const parsed = new URL(raw);
const c = parsed.searchParams.get('continue');
```

4. Pass the decoded value through the current helper:

```js
function routeContinue(url, fallback) {
  return (!url || !url.startsWith('/') || url.startsWith('//')) ? fallback : url;
}
const location = routeContinue(c, '/photos');
console.log(location);
console.log(new URL(location, 'https://immich.local').href);
```

Observed result:

```json
{
  "searchParamContinue": "/\\evil.example/oauth-callback",
  "routeContinueReturn": "/\\evil.example/oauth-callback",
  "browserResolved": "https://evil.example/oauth-callback"
}
```

5. The login load path uses the returned value as a redirect location for already-authenticated users:

```ts
const continueUrl = Route.continue(url.searchParams.get('continue'), Route.photos());

if (authManager.authenticated) {
  redirect(307, continueUrl);
}
```

## Browser evidence

A local Chrome proof served `307 Location: /\\127.0.0.1:<port>/pwn?marker=slash-backslash` from `http://localhost:<port>/start`. Chrome followed the redirect as a network request to host `127.0.0.1:<port>`, not `localhost:<port>`, and rendered the destination page. The recorded requests were:

```json
[
  {"path":"/start","host":"localhost:<port>"},
  {"path":"/pwn?marker=slash-backslash","host":"127.0.0.1:<port>"}
]
```

This demonstrates that a browser follows the slash-backslash Location value as an authority-changing redirect.

## Root cause

`Route.continue` performs string prefix checks before any URL normalization. It rejects protocol-relative values beginning with `//`, but it does not reject backslashes. Browsers normalize backslashes as slashes for special schemes during URL processing, so `/\evil.example/path` is effectively treated like `//evil.example/path` by the browser even though it bypasses the helper's `startsWith('//')` check.

## Remediation

Reject backslashes before returning a continuation URL, or parse the value against the deployment origin and require the parsed origin to match the Immich origin before using the value in a redirect or navigation sink.

For example:

```ts
continue: (url: string | null, fallback: string) => {
  if (!url || url.includes('\\') || !url.startsWith('/') || url.startsWith('//')) {
    return fallback;
  }

  return url;
}
```

A stronger fix is to normalize with `new URL(url, origin)` and return only values whose parsed origin equals the expected Immich origin.", "ghsa_id": "GHSA-qp2h-w794-2vhf", "html_url": "https://github.com/immich-app/immich/security/advisories/GHSA-qp2h-w794-2vhf", "identifiers": [{"type": "GHSA", "value": "GHSA-qp2h-w794-2vhf"}], "private_fork": null, "published_at": "2026-07-06T09:50:45Z", "publisher": {"avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11602424?v=4", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/events{/privacy}", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/gists{/gist_id}", "gravatar_id": "", "html_url": "https://github.com/bo0tzz", "id": 11602424, "login": "bo0tzz", "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNjAyNDI0", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/orgs", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/received_events", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/repos", "site_admin": false, "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz/subscriptions", "type": "User", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bo0tzz", "user_view_type": "public"}, "severity": "medium", "state": "published", "submission": null, "summary": "Incomplete fix for login continue redirect allows slash-backslash open redirect", "updated_at": "2026-07-06T09:50:45Z", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/immich-app/immich/security-advisories/GHSA-qp2h-w794-2vhf", "vulnerabilities": [{"package": {"ecosystem": "other", "name": "immich-app/immich"}, "patched_versions": "v3.0.0", "vulnerable_functions": [], "vulnerable_version_range": "<= 2.7.5, and current main e2de8c7c536cac5a673a3aa60cc998815b62d247 after PR #28706"}], "withdrawn_at": null}
